id: pm-atfm
title: "Context relevance evaluation harness: graded golden-workspace judgments for pm context/next quality"
description: "Evaluation harness for context quality: graded workspaces and continuity scenarios that measure whether pm context/next return the right items under explicit token budgets."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: context,quality-gate,relevance,scale
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:25:57.317Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T23:52:06.951Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: Golden corpus (one real-shaped and one synthetic pm-mi2x workspace) with graded judgments versioned in-repo; offline runner scores pm context and pm next with rank-aware quality metrics; baseline of the current structural assembler recorded before pm-4k6b lands; CI gate fails on quality regression beyond a documented threshold; harness consumes only public SDK read primitives; documented workflow for adding new judgment cases
